      <hedline>
        <hl1>A 12-Year-Old Boy, Killed in Gaza</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John R Wisdom letter deplores killing of 12-year-old boy in Gaza (Oct 1 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mideast Violence Continues to Rage; Death Toll Rises'' (front page, Oct. 1):</p>
        <p>Could there be a more passionate plea for the immediate resumption and success of peace talks in the Middle East than the horrible pictures of the death of a little boy in Gaza?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mideast Violence Continues to Rage; Death Toll Rises'' (front page, Oct. 1):</p>
        <p>Could there be a more passionate plea for the immediate resumption and success of peace talks in the Middle East than the horrible pictures of the death of a little boy in Gaza?</p>
        <p>That grown men brandish their religion as excuse for actions that kill children in their parents' arms disgusts me. As an American Jew and a father, I am further revolted by the fact that the idealists and heretics were led in this instance by the extremist Ariel Sharon.</p>
        <p>I pray that our new year, just begun, brings with it a greater respect for the life of every son and daughter, a choice of humanity over hatred, tolerance over terrorism. I must for my own sanity assume that every father feels the pain of that father in Gaza.</p>
        <p>JOHN R. WISDOM  Scarsdale, N.Y., Oct. 1, 2000</p>
      </block>
